libplctag
------------------------------------------
This library for Linux and Windows (not heavily tested) provides a means of
accessing PLCs to read and write simple data.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-2
  libplctag-devel-2.1.17-1bl1
  libplctag2.1-2.1.17-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-2
  ninja-1.10.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/libplctag/libplctag

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/libplctag/libplctag/archive/v2.1.17.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libplctag-2.1.17-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libplctag-2.1.17-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libplctag-2.1.17-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libplctag-2.1.17-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libplctag2.1-2.1.17-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libplctag-devel-2.1.17-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

